## Project Ideas

- [ ] Extend one of the CodePath projects?  
      - [ ] **Expense tracking app**  
- [ ] Maybe think of target audience/demographic (e.g. business owners, casual users, etc.) so it’s easier for us to determine which features to prioritize/implement  
- [ ] Potential ideas to implement  
      - [ ] Expense tracking  
      - [ ] Home page (with home icon/button at the bottom)  
      - [ ] Overview page with \[circle\] graphs displaying expenses (also has icon/button at bottom)  
      - [ ] Plus (**\+**) icon/button at bottom to add expense/etc.  
      - [ ] Profile and/or settings page (maybe) (also has icon/button at bottom)  
      - [ ] Account sign up and log in (probably using **mysql** or **back4app**)  
            - [ ] Local authentication framework (Local FaceID/Biometric Login)  
      - [ ] Notifications page/tab (maybe) (also has icon/button at bottom)  
      - [ ] Expense difference tracking (how expenses differ from one week/month to another, mean expenses on food, gas, etc.)  
      - [ ] Option to create budgets and keep track of them/notify when the budget is exceeded or close to being exceeded.  
      - [ ] Separate expenses by category (maybe) (e.g. food/drink, traveling, entertainment, bills/taxes, etc.)  
      - [ ] Tags feature; similar to categories, except users can define the tag  
      - [ ] Automated receipt capture (maybe) i.e. user scans/provides image of receipt (be it irl or a screenshot, etc.) and the app uses CV (computer vision) \+ NLP (natural language processing) to extract receipt data and add as an expense  
      - [ ] Daily/weekly/etc. tips providing useful financial tips, etc. (maybe) can be pre-defined or even AI-generated, assuming we decide to implement it?  
      - [ ] Calendar or something to show spending per week, month, etc.? (maybe)  
      - [ ] Option to export data as .csv (or other format) that user can use in Excel (maybe)  
      - [ ] Light and dark mode (maybe)  
            - [ ] using .systemBackground (Based on IOS Preferences/Manual?)  
      - [ ] Graphing and Data vizualization framework (Generating graphs based on user data)
